Hypermarcas SA , Brazilâ€™s fourth-
largest consumer goods company by market value, agreed to pay
251.5 million reais ($147 million) for three separate
acquisitions.  Hypermarcas agreed to buy the Digedrat, Peridal and
Lopigrel prescription drug brands from Medley Industria
Farmaceutica Ltda. for 84 million reais, it said in a regulatory
filing today. The Sao Paulo-based company also plans to acquire
the Pom Pom soap brand from Colgate-Palmolive Co. for 85 million
reais, according to a separate filing.  In a third filing, Hypermarcas said it signed a memorandum
of understanding to pay 82.5 million reais for IPH&C Industria
de Produtos de Higiene e Cosmeticos Ltda., DPH Distribuidora de
Produtos de Higiene Ltda. e Comercial Maripa Ltda., dental-
hygiene companies that sell products under the Bitufo brand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
